  Given a formal topology <fr:tex>\mathcal {A}  = (S,  \sqsubseteq ,  \lhd )</fr:tex>, a subset <fr:tex>A    \subseteq  S</fr:tex> is called saturated if it is a fixed point of the <fr:link
href="axt-000D.xml"
type="local"
addr="axt-000D">closure
  operator</fr:link> associated with <fr:tex>\mathcal {A}</fr:tex>, which is to say it satisfies
  <fr:tex
display="block">\mathsf {Clos} _{ \mathcal {A} }(A) = A.</fr:tex></fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree></fr:backlinks><fr:references></fr:references></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>